Include a feature to add a branch to a review via REST API, similar to [https://docs.atlassian.com/fisheye-crucible/latest/wadl/crucible.html#rest-service:reviews-v1:id:addChangeset].
h3. Workaround

This feature already exists, although is not documented in official [REST API docs|https://docs.atlassian.com/fisheye-crucible/latest/wadl/fecru.html].

The 'Branch Review Plugin' which is always bundled with Crucible contains an endpoint:

{noformat}POST [https://FISHEYE_URL/rest/branchreview/latest/trackedbranch/|https://fisheye_url/rest/branchreview/latest/trackedbranch/]<REVIEW_PERM_ID> {noformat}

with JSON payload in a body like:
{noformat}
{
  "autoUpdate": true,
  "baseBranch": "trunk",
  "reviewedBranch": "atlassian-seraph-2.5.x",
  "repositoryName": "atlassian-public"
} {noformat}
 

See 

[https://community.atlassian.com/t5/Answers-Developer-Questions/Adding-a-Branch-to-a-Code-Review-from-a-Crucible-Add-On/qaq-p/524214] for details.

