Few scenarios identified:
If you create a review with a search result, and you used either {{Before Date}} or {{After Date}}, if you select {{Add all X revisions}}, it will fail with the following error:

{noformat}
error parsing query: expecting DATE, found 'null'
{noformat}

Performing the above steps by selecting an {{Author}} and then selecting {{Add all X revisions}} results in an error message such as:

{noformat}
error parsing query: unexpected <EOF> at character 44
{noformat}

Steps to reproduce:

# Create a review.
# Select {{Search for files}}.
# Select a repository.
# Select a {{Before:}} date of today, or an {{Author}}
# Click {{Search}}
# Click {{Add all X revisions}}.

It also affects advanced search, as explained in https://answers.atlassian.com/questions/12157207/adding-content-to-a-crucible-review-using-eyeql-error-parsing-query-expecting-eq-found-null , steps to reproduce:
# click {{+}} to add content
# select {{Search for Files}}
# click {{Switch to advanced search}}
# enter an EyeQL query: {{select revisions where csid = C}} where C is an existing P4 changeset ID (same with other SCMs)
# click {{Search}}
# click {{Add all N revisions}}
an error message is shown: 

{noformat}
error parsing query: expecting EQ, found 'null'
{noformat}

When creating a Branch Review in Crucible it is stated that;

{quote}
Reviewers will only see the changes that have been made on the branch – irrelevant changes are hidden.
{quote}

* [Adding content to the review|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CRUCIBLE/Adding+content+to+the+review#Addingcontenttothereview-Branches]

However if you create the branch review while FishEye is performing an incremental indexing on the repo (i.e. when it is still in the scanning phase.) or when using *custom symbolic rules* then changes made to the trunk (which may have already been reviewed) are displayed also.

A consequence of this can be that a Branch review is unable to be created due to the 800 file revision limit being breached as all the revisions present on the branch are pulled through;

!Screen Shot 2015-02-10 at 11.47.59.png|thumbnail!

Crucible review email subjects are currently truncated to 50 characters. Allow this character limit to be customizable.

The current 50 character limit includes both the issue key and title, if the review key is long, it can cause the title of the review to be truncated without much context. For example:

{code}[Crucible] toolchain-depot2-toolchain-442: Adding a regressio...{code}

Before 3.0, the review key was not part of the 50 character limit:

{code}[Crucible] State changed to Review: (orbis-cpu-toolchain-414) Revert dev/trunk revision 1832 (was: cherry-pick U...{code}

